node.text:
https://smittenkitchen.com/2007/10/butternut-squash-and-caramelized-onion-galette/

Did you miss my IG Live demo of making smittenkitchen.com's butternut squash and caramelized onion galette on Friday, 11/8? Good news! We finally figured out how to share and save it forever on IGTV (thank you to everyone who DMed me with tips). Hope you make it, too! [Butternut Squash and Caramelized Onion Galette on smittenkitchen.com]

node.text: Feeling celebratory because I just handed in my manuscript for #smittenkitchenkeepers, a new cookbook for Fall 2022. I can't wait to tell you more about it -- but first, some cake. This eight-layer beauty tastes like caramel graham crackers with a creamy, slightly tangy filling and it's one of the coziest things I've ever made. // Russian Honey Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: A surprising win in the Dinners For Everyone category, a classic cobb lets everyone at my table assemble their salads exactly the way they want it. In the summer, if I have access to a grill, I grill both the chicken and the bacon to keep the kitchen as cool as possible. // Classic Cobb Salad on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: If you can read about something called a magic cobbler that you make more or less entirely in the pan you bake it and not have it in the oven 15 minutes later, you're made of stronger stuff than me. This one celebrates peak late-summer-ness with apples, plums and a cinnamon-sugar lid and it's exquisite served with whatever is left of a scoop of vanilla ice cream after it lands on top of the warm cobbler. // Magic Apple and Plum Cobbler on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: Wait, come back! I realize that homemade cream cheese may not have been on your agenda, possibly ever, but this is almost criminally easy and fast to make, requiring not a single fancy or random ingredient, and the taste is unparalleled, especially in the flavored cream cheeses. You're going to love it. // Homemade Cream Cheese on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. node.text: A thing I've noticed this week is that a lot of people are keenly interested in transitioning to fall foods while I, stubbornly, would like it to be summer for at least the 11 days left in it, and possibly as long as the good tomatoes last. Fortunately, this marriage of American-style tomato soup and French-style onion soup -- that's basically an open-faced grilled cheese sandwich on top -- has something for everyone, no matter what season we're planted in. // Roasted Tomato Soup with Broiled Cheddar on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: What if I don't want to make dinner but I really want to make a chocolate pudding pie instead? Is this an option? Can you tell I'm on deadline? I'm not exactly asking for a friend. The cold, richness of homemade chocolate pudding in a crisp, buttery pie shell with a raft of whipped cream and confetti of chocolate shavings on top beckon, and I think we need to listen. // Chocolate Pudding Pie on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: Feta, tomatoes, garlic, and chickpeas roast in olive oil until the tomatoes blister and soften, the feta becomes creamy, and the whole mixture is a dream to scoop onto flatbread. It's almost endlessly tweakable and I bet even better now with in-season tomatoes. Dinner should always be this easy. // Baked Feta with Tomatoes and Chickpeas on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. Click the link "smittenkitchen.com/instagram" Click the photo for the recipe you want and it will take you to it.

node.text: An Ottolenghi take on baked pasta with tomatoes, parmesan and enough mozzarella that it stretches from each forkful, but there are also pillows of eggplant and other vegetables, so it doesn't feel over the top. The leftovers, should any survive, are luxurious. // Baked Orzo with Eggplant and Mozzarella on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. node.text: Dry, beleaguered honey cake is no way to kick off 5782. This best-in-category classic from Marcy Goldman is the kind you make every year -- deeply spiced, great crumb, and very cozy. It gets better as it has time to rest, honestly, just like me. // Majestic and Moist Honey Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile.
